09/11/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Newly-appointed Defence Minister Sorin Frunzaverde ruled out the possibility Wednesday (November 8th) of withdrawing troops from Iraq for the time being.
He also announced that the defence ministry obtained a 15% increase in its 2007 budget.
Frunzaverde is the replacement for Teodor Atanasiu, who resigned recently after a lengthy dispute with ruling coalition partners.
In other news, a simulation military drill titled "SEESIM 06", aimed at improving inter-operability in reaction to natural disasters in the region, began on Wednesday in Bucharest and Skopje.
The exercise includes troops from the countries of the South Eastern Europe Defence Ministerial Process.
(Antena 3 TV, Mediafax, Rompres - 08/11/06)
